        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Domain Driven Design is an architecture approach with a strong orientation towards the business domain.\nIt is based largely on a book by Eric Evans (",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 20, "column": 1, "offset": 277 },
            "end": { "line": 21, "column": 46, "offset": 426 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "title": null,
          "url": "https://www.domainlanguage.com/ddd/blue-book/[blue",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "https://www.domainlanguage.com/ddd/blue-book/[blue",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 21, "column": 46, "offset": 426 },
                "end": { "line": 21, "column": 96, "offset": 476 },
                "indent": []
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 21, "column": 46, "offset": 426 },
            "end": { "line": 21, "column": 96, "offset": 476 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " book]), later on refined by a book from Vaughn Vernon detailing the concrete implementation of DDD in an organization (",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 21, "column": 96, "offset": 476 },
            "end": { "line": 21, "column": 216, "offset": 596 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "title": null,
          "url": "https://kalele.io/books/[red",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "https://kalele.io/books/[red",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 21, "column": 216, "offset": 596 },
                "end": { "line": 21, "column": 244, "offset": 624 },
                "indent": []
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 21, "column": 216, "offset": 596 },
            "end": { "line": 21, "column": 244, "offset": 624 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " book]).\nIts goal is to establish a ubitiqous language across domain and IT experts based on which the architecture or design of a system can be build.\nThe following figure gives an overview of what DDD is about.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 21, "column": 244, "offset": 624 },
            "end": { "line": 23, "column": 61, "offset": 836 },
            "indent": [1, 1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
