        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The goal of strategic design is to decompose a large, complex domain into subdomains and consequently each subdomain into bounded contexts.\nDependencies between bounded contexts are then explicitly traced in a context map and implemented by using one of the provided strategic design patterns.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 30, "column": 1, "offset": 1245 },
            "end": { "line": 31, "column": 154, "offset": 1538 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 30, "column": 1, "offset": 1245 },
        "end": { "line": 31, "column": 154, "offset": 1538 },
        "indent": [1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "== Decomposition into subdomains",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 33, "column": 1, "offset": 1540 },
            "end": { "line": 33, "column": 33, "offset": 1572 },
            "indent": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 33, "column": 1, "offset": 1540 },
        "end": { "line": 33, "column": 33, "offset": 1572 },
        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The actual decomposition into subdomains is a business architecture topic and several methods for this exist.\nMost notably big picture event storming can be used as a collaborative format for identification of subdomains.\nTypical candidates for this are the parts of the big picture between pivotal events and swim lanes (s. link:",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 35, "column": 1, "offset": 1574 },
            "end": { "line": 37, "column": 109, "offset": 1904 },
            "indent": [1, 1]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "title": null,
          "url": "https://www.eventstorming.com/[Event",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "https://www.eventstorming.com/[Event",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 37, "column": 109, "offset": 1904 },
                "end": { "line": 37, "column": 145, "offset": 1940 },
                "indent": []
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 37, "column": 109, "offset": 1904 },
            "end": { "line": 37, "column": 145, "offset": 1940 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " Storming]).\nEach subdomain thus identified can be classified into one of the following:",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 37, "column": 145, "offset": 1940 },
            "end": { "line": 38, "column": 76, "offset": 2028 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 35, "column": 1, "offset": 1574 },
        "end": { "line": 38, "column": 76, "offset": 2028 },
        "indent": [1, 1, 1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Core subdomain:: the true business of a company, where it differentiates itself in a unique way from competitors in a complex context.\nThe uniqueness necessitates that no existing software exists to support the business as done by the company.\nIt brings a competitive advantage and therefore the willingness to invest in this subdomain, since it can yield a positive ROI.\nSupporting subdomain:: the part of the business where no off-the-shelf product implementing this functionality exists, but where the company cannot really gain a competitive advantage.\nCaution is advised in those cases where a supporting subdomain is becoming complex, because it is then actually becoming a core domain, or the added complexity should be questioned against the business value.\nGeneric subdomain:: the part of the business, where industry solutions simply exist and no gain in own solutions can be identified.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 40, "column": 1, "offset": 2030 },
            "end": { "line": 45, "column": 132, "offset": 2927 },
            "indent": [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 40, "column": 1, "offset": 2030 },
        "end": { "line": 45, "column": 132, "offset": 2927 },
        "indent": [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "A very good, more detailed explanation on the above can be found link:",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 47, "column": 1, "offset": 2929 },
            "end": { "line": 47, "column": 71, "offset": 2999 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "title": null,
          "url": "https://vladikk.com/2018/01/26/revisiting-the-basics-of-ddd/[here]",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "https://vladikk.com/2018/01/26/revisiting-the-basics-of-ddd/[here]",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 47, "column": 71, "offset": 2999 },
                "end": { "line": 47, "column": 137, "offset": 3065 },
