    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "== Decomposition into bounded contexts",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 54, "column": 1, "offset": 3370 },
            "end": { "line": 54, "column": 39, "offset": 3408 },
            "indent": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 54, "column": 1, "offset": 3370 },
        "end": { "line": 54, "column": 39, "offset": 3408 },
        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Whereas the domain and its subdomains purely address the problem space of a business challenge, bounded contexts aim at the solutions space.\nTypically within a large domain, the ubitiqous language cannot be applied canonically across all contexts.\nBetween the different subdomain different understandings on the same terms may exist.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 56, "column": 1, "offset": 3410 },
            "end": { "line": 58, "column": 86, "offset": 3743 },
            "indent": [1, 1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 56, "column": 1, "offset": 3410 },
        "end": { "line": 58, "column": 86, "offset": 3743 },
        "indent": [1, 1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "A typical example would be the customer: the sales subdomain handles a customer in a completely different way then the after sales.\nFor the sales subdomain the business opportunities and how to actually win them is important.\nThe after-sales subdomain is interested however in the bought products and what service level the customer acquired.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 60, "column": 1, "offset": 3745 },
            "end": { "line": 62, "column": 117, "offset": 4087 },
            "indent": [1, 1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 60, "column": 1, "offset": 3745 },
        "end": { "line": 62, "column": 117, "offset": 4087 },
        "indent": [1, 1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "DDD does not aim towards a holistic ubitiqous language, but realistically only aims towards such a common language understanding in a ",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 64, "column": 1, "offset": 4089 },
            "end": { "line": 64, "column": 135, "offset": 4223 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "emphasis",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "bounded context",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 64, "column": 136, "offset": 4224 },
                "end": { "line": 64, "column": 151, "offset": 4239 },
                "indent": []
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 64, "column": 135, "offset": 4223 },
            "end": { "line": 64, "column": 152, "offset": 4240 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ".",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 64, "column": 152, "offset": 4240 },
            "end": { "line": 64, "column": 153, "offset": 4241 },
            "indent": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 64, "column": 1, "offset": 4089 },
        "end": { "line": 64, "column": 153, "offset": 4241 },
        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Bounded Context:: the bounded context establishes a ubitiqous language expressed via a domain model in a single subdomain",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 66, "column": 1, "offset": 4243 },
            "end": { "line": 66, "column": 122, "offset": 4364 },
            "indent": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 66, "column": 1, "offset": 4243 },
        "end": { "line": 66, "column": 122, "offset": 4364 },
        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The core design task in strategic DDD is to identify these bounded contexts and then to relate them with each other where dependencies between them exist.\nFor identification event storming is again recommended within the industry and also by ADAM.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 68, "column": 1, "offset": 4366 },
            "end": { "line": 69, "column": 93, "offset": 4613 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 68, "column": 1, "offset": 4366 },
        "end": { "line": 69, "column": 93, "offset": 4613 },
        "indent": [1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "They can be further defined by using a canvas approach as for instance this one (ADAM also provides an own version of this):",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 71, "column": 1, "offset": 4615 },
            "end": { "line": 71, "column": 125, "offset": 4739 },
            "indent": []
          }
        }
      ],
