      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 73, "column": 1, "offset": 4741 },
        "end": { "line": 74, "column": 118, "offset": 4953 },
        "indent": [1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "For each bounded context, a different architecture can then make sense depending on the requirements and also the subdomain it lies in.\nIt is especially noteworthy, that link:../../micro_architecture/backend/tactical_ddd/tactical_ddd.html",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 76, "column": 1, "offset": 4955 },
            "end": { "line": 77, "column": 103, "offset": 5193 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "linkReference",
          "identifier": "tactical ddd",
          "referenceType": "shortcut",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Tactical DDD",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 77, "column": 104, "offset": 5194 },
                "end": { "line": 77, "column": 116, "offset": 5206 },
                "indent": []
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 77, "column": 103, "offset": 5193 },
            "end": { "line": 77, "column": 117, "offset": 5207 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " is often seen as especially valuable for the core subdomain.\nFor bounded contexts in generic or supporting subdomains, a simple CRUD-based or low code architecture might be a better choice.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 77, "column": 117, "offset": 5207 },
            "end": { "line": 78, "column": 129, "offset": 5397 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 76, "column": 1, "offset": 4955 },
        "end": { "line": 78, "column": 129, "offset": 5397 },
        "indent": [1, 1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "== Context Mapping",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 80, "column": 1, "offset": 5399 },
            "end": { "line": 80, "column": 19, "offset": 5417 },
            "indent": []
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 80, "column": 1, "offset": 5399 },
        "end": { "line": 80, "column": 19, "offset": 5417 },
        "indent": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Bounded contexts do not exist standalone, but depend on each other and thus require integration.\nStrategic design defines different patterns for mapping and integrating one context with others as can be seen from the overview above.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 82, "column": 1, "offset": 5419 },
            "end": { "line": 83, "column": 136, "offset": 5651 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 82, "column": 1, "offset": 5419 },
        "end": { "line": 83, "column": 136, "offset": 5651 },
        "indent": [1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Again we only point to the link:",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 85, "column": 1, "offset": 5653 },
            "end": { "line": 85, "column": 33, "offset": 5685 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "title": null,
          "url": "https://www.domainlanguage.com/ddd/reference/[DDD",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "https://www.domainlanguage.com/ddd/reference/[DDD",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 85, "column": 33, "offset": 5685 },
                "end": { "line": 85, "column": 82, "offset": 5734 },
                "indent": []
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 85, "column": 33, "offset": 5685 },
            "end": { "line": 85, "column": 82, "offset": 5734 },
            "indent": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " Reference] for the definition of those patterns and to this summary given below by the DDD crew.\nADAM in addition provides guidance on how contexts can be related between each other.",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 85, "column": 82, "offset": 5734 },
            "end": { "line": 86, "column": 86, "offset": 5917 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": { "line": 85, "column": 1, "offset": 5653 },
        "end": { "line": 86, "column": 86, "offset": 5917 },
        "indent": [1]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ".Summary of context map patterns\nimage:",
          "position": {
            "start": { "line": 88, "column": 1, "offset": 5919 },
            "end": { "line": 89, "column": 7, "offset": 5958 },
            "indent": [1]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "title": null,
          "url": "https://github.com/ddd-crew/ddd-starter-modelling-process/raw/master/resources/context-map-cheat-sheet.png[",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "https://github.com/ddd-crew/ddd-starter-modelling-process/raw/master/resources/context-map-cheat-sheet.png[",
              "position": {
                "start": { "line": 89, "column": 7, "offset": 5958 },
